1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of fog computing as an extension to cloud computing for IoT networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.SD (Software Development) - The paper proposes a new IoT-based sensing framework for urban sound classification, which involves software development and implementation. 

3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper mentions the use of an urban sound classification model, which involves machine learning techniques. 

4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the allocation of resources in the network for effective management of crowdsensing and real-time data, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 

5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions the issue of data management constraints in fog computing, which may involve security concerns.
